<paragraph blockId="80.[192,1440,1123,1211]" pageId="80" pageNumber="77">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[192,315,1123,1147]" pageId="80" pageNumber="77">Remarks</emphasis>
. 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon and Canepari" authorityYear="2013" box="[330,562,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Serratitibia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="tammy">
<emphasis box="[330,562,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="77">Serratitibia tammy</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
has an elytral pattern slightly resembling specimens of 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Gordon and Canepari" authorityYear="2013" box="[1240,1374,1123,1147]" class="Insecta" family="Coccinellidae" genus="Serratitibia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Coleoptera" pageId="80" pageNumber="77" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="kathleen">
<emphasis box="[1240,1258,1124,1147]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="77">S</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[1271,1374,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="80" pageNumber="77">kathleen</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[192,303,1155,1179]" name="Trinidad and Tobago" pageId="80" pageNumber="77">Trinidad</collectingCountry>
, but the latter species has both elytral spots highly irregular, the result of coalescing of normally discrete spots.
</paragraph>
